  • Package jv.anim

    • Class jv.anim.PsAnimation extends PsObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • m_dynamicList

          java.util.Vector<E> m_dynamicList
          Hashtable of time listeners.

        • m_modal

          boolean m_modal
          Flag is animation is modal such that the start method blocks until this animation has stopped.

        • m_globalTime

          double m_globalTime
          Global time of the external animation. If dynamic object of 'this' shall be frozen to a specific time, then set m_syncFlag==false. In such a case, m_currentTime shows the time of the dynamic object.

        • m_currentTime

          PuDouble m_currentTime
          Current time of the dynamic object. If m_syncFlag==false current time may be different from m_globalTime.

        • m_speedType

          int m_speedType
          Speed type of animation, possible values FORWARD, REWIND, FAST_FORWARD, FAST_REWIND.

        • m_timeIncr

          double m_timeIncr
          Time increment equals +/-m_currentTime.line/page increments.

        • m_sleepInterval

          long m_sleepInterval
          Sleep interval length between two timer events.

        • m_repeat

          int m_repeat
          Determines repeat mode, possible values ONE_WAY, LOOP, BACK_FORTH.

        • m_syncFlag

          boolean m_syncFlag
          Synchronize with global time if true. Flag is initialized during construction if user forgets to create constructor in the right way, i.e. forgets to call method init().

        • m_enableKeys

          boolean m_enableKeys
          Set visibility of key buttons prevKey, nextKey etc. in animation panel.

        • m_interpolType

          int m_interpolType
          Set visibility of key buttons prevKey, nextKey etc. in animation panel.

        • m_position

          int[] m_position
          Default position and size of animation dialog.

  • Package jv.geom

    • Class jv.geom.PgBndConstraint extends PsObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • m_dim

          int m_dim
          Dimension of vertices and vectors used as constraints.

        • m_shape

          java.util.BitSet m_shape
          Bitset contains all flags of this constraint.

        • m_start

          PdVector m_start
          Start point of boundary, first vertex.

        • m_end

          PdVector m_end
          End point of boundary, last vertex.

        • m_vec1

          PdVector m_vec1
          Additional control vertex, meaning depends on current shape.

        • m_vec2

          PdVector m_vec2
          Additional control vertex, meaning depends on current shape.

        • m_dir

          PdVector m_dir
          Unit direction of constraining line or unit normal of constraining plane.

        • m_startDir

          PdVector m_startDir
          Special constraint for the first point of boundary, for example, two adjacent planar curves force the common vertex to lie on the straight line along which both plane intersect. If this instance variable is null, then there is no constraint.

        • m_endDir

          PdVector m_endDir
          Special constraint for the last point of boundary, for example, two adjacent planar curves force the common vertex to lie on the straight line along which both plane intersect. If this instance variable is null, then there is no constraint.

    • Class jv.geom.PgBndPolygon extends PgPolygon implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • m_geom

          PgElementSet m_geom
          Polyhedral surface which has 'this' as boundary, i.e. the base surface.

        • m_vertexInd

          PiVector m_vertexInd
          Indices of vertices in the corresponding vertex array of the underlying base surface. The geometric vertices of this boundary polygon are then copies of surface vertices of the base surface.

        • m_elementInd

          PiVector m_elementInd
          Elements of the base surface adjacent to boundary edges.

        • m_neighbourLocInd

          PiVector m_neighbourLocInd
          Local index of m_geom.m_neighbour referencing to boundary edge.

        • m_bConforming

          boolean m_bConforming
          Flag whether boundary refers to a non-conforming elementSet and has been updated.

        • m_bShowIndividualMaterial

          boolean m_bShowIndividualMaterial
          Flag if individual material of vf or of pointSet is used.

        • m_bndConstraint

          PgBndConstraint m_bndConstraint
          Constraints describing how the boundary is allowed to move when varying the surface. E.g. boundary may be fixed, constraint to a line or to a plane, and others.

    • Class jv.geom.PgEdgeStar extends PiVector implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • m_maxValence

          int m_maxValence
          Maximal number of assigned adjacent elements.

        • m_valence

          int m_valence
          Current number of assigned adjacent elements.

        • m_elementInd

          int[] m_elementInd
          Element indices containing edge. There may be more than two elements joining an edge, but only two elements are allowed for manifold polyhedrons.

        • m_neighbourLocInd

          int[] m_neighbourLocInd
          Local index of vertex in each element such that neighbour value of vertex references to the neighbouring element at this edge. I.e. triang.m_neighbour[elemInd].m_data[m_neighbourLocInd] = index of adjacent element

    • Class jv.geom.PgElementSet extends PgPointSet implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • m_bShowEdgeLabels

          boolean m_bShowEdgeLabels
          Flag whether labels of edges are shown in display.

        • m_bShowElementLabels

          boolean m_bShowElementLabels
          Flag whether labels of elements are shown in display.

        • m_dimOfElements

          int m_dimOfElements
          Determines size of elements. It has the following states m_dimOfElement = -1 elements have different size = 3 all elements are triangles = 4 all elements are quadrilaterals = .. all elements are polygons with same size Some methods assume all elements to be triangles. In such a case all elements are triangulated.
          See Also:
          PgElementSet.setDimOfElements(int)

        • m_maxDimOfElements

          int m_maxDimOfElements
          Maximal number of vertices per element.

        • m_numElements

          int m_numElements
          Number of used elements. Each element may be a polygon of different size.
          See Also:
          PgElementSet.setNumElements(int)

        • m_maxNumElements

          int m_maxNumElements
          Number of allocated elements, in contrast to the number of used elements. This value is adjusted automatically whenever more memory is needed.

        • m_element

          PiVector[] m_element
          Array with all polygonal elements. Each element with, say k, vertices is given by the indices of its k vertices in array '[] m_vertex' of the superclass. Elements may have different number of edges.

        • m_elementColor

          java.awt.Color[] m_elementColor
          Array with a color of each element. Used in display if array is not null.

        • m_elementBackColor

          java.awt.Color[] m_elementBackColor
          Array with a color of each backside element. Used in display if array is not null.

        • m_elementNormal

          PdVector[] m_elementNormal
          Array with a normal per element.

        • m_neighbour

          PiVector[] m_neighbour
          Array with neighbours of all elements. For each element with, say k, edges exists a corresponding neighbour array listing the indices of the neighbouring elements at these edges. See method makeNeighbour() for details on usage.

        • m_bndList

          PgBndPolygon[] m_bndList
          Array with boundary polygons. Each polygon may have boundary constraints.

        • m_selectedBndPolygon

          PgBndPolygon m_selectedBndPolygon
          Currently selected boundary polygon.

        • m_bShowBoundaries

          boolean m_bShowBoundaries
          Flag whether boundaries are shown in display.

        • m_bShowTaggedBoundaries

          boolean m_bShowTaggedBoundaries
          Flag whether tagged boundaries are shown in display.

        • m_globalBndColor

          PdColor m_globalBndColor
          Global color of boundary used in display.

        • m_globalBndTagColor

          PdColor m_globalBndTagColor
          Global color of tagged boundary used in display.

        • m_globalBndSize

          PuDouble m_globalBndSize
          Thickness in pixels of boundary edges used in display.

        • m_bConforming

          boolean m_bConforming
          Indicates whether triangulation is in edge midpoint or vertex (true) representation.

        • m_elementSaved

          PiVector[] m_elementSaved
          Saved original vertex indices of elements of vertex based triangulation.

        • m_savedNumVertices

          int m_savedNumVertices
          Saved number of vertices of vertex based triangulation.

        • m_bShowElementTexture

          boolean m_bShowElementTexture
          Show element texture.

        • m_elementTexture

          PdVector[][] m_elementTexture
          Texture coordinates for each element.

        • m_bShowSilhouette

          boolean m_bShowSilhouette
          Flag whether edges at horizon are shown thickened in display.

        • m_bEnableEdges

          boolean m_bEnableEdges
          Determines if list of edges is maintained as instance variable.
          Since:
          JavaView 3.96.026

        • m_numEdgeStars

          int m_numEdgeStars
          Number of used edges. Each edge may be a polygon of different size.

        • m_edgeStar

          PgEdgeStar[] m_edgeStar
          Array with edges of element set. Will be updated whenever connectivity changes. Use makeEdgeStars() or makeNeighbour() to generate edge array.

        • m_edgeColor

          java.awt.Color[] m_edgeColor
          Color of each edge. Optionally, the edge colors may also be induced from either element or vertex colors if available.
          Since:
          JavaView 3.96.026

        • m_edgeSize

          PdVector m_edgeSize
          Thickness of each edge measured as radius of the representing circle or glyph.
          Since:
          JavaView 3.96.026

        • m_elementEdge

          PiVector[] m_elementEdge
          For each element, the indices of the incident edges in the same enumeration as the neighbour array.
          Since:
          JavaView 3.96.026

        • m_bShowEdges

          boolean m_bShowEdges
          Flag whether edges are shown in display.

        • m_bShowTaggedEdges

          boolean m_bShowTaggedEdges
          Flag whether tagged edges are shown in display.

        • m_bShowEdgeColors

          boolean m_bShowEdgeColors
          Flag if global color of edges used in display, applied if no individual edge coloring available.

        • m_bShowEdgeColorFromElements

          boolean m_bShowEdgeColorFromElements
          Flag if edge colors are induced from element colors.

        • m_bShowEdgeColorFromVertices

          boolean m_bShowEdgeColorFromVertices
          Flag if edge colors are induced from vertex colors.

        • m_globalEdgeColor

          PdColor m_globalEdgeColor
          Global color of edges used in display, applied if no individual edge coloring available.

        • m_globalEdgeTagColor

          PdColor m_globalEdgeTagColor
          Global color of tagged edges used in display.

        • m_globalEdgeSize

          PuDouble m_globalEdgeSize
          Thickness in pixels of each edge used in display.

        • m_bShowEdgeSizes

          boolean m_bShowEdgeSizes
          Flag whether to show individual or global edge thickness.
          Since:
          JavaView 3.96.026

        • m_creaseAngle

          PuDouble m_creaseAngle
          Crease angle is a threshold determining sharp crease edges. In smooth lighting and shading there is no interpolation across crease edges. An edge is a crease edge if the dihedral angle (positive angle between normals) between the two adjacent faces is equal or larger than the crease angle threshold. The crease angle is measure in radians in [0,Pi]. A crease angle 0 induces flat shading and prevents all smoothing, and a crease angle Pi+eps shows all edges with smooth shading.
          Since:
          JavaView 3.03.007

        • m_bShowElements

          boolean m_bShowElements
          Flag whether elements are shown in display.

        • m_bShowTaggedElements

          boolean m_bShowTaggedElements
          Flag whether to show tagged elements or not.

        • m_bShowBackface

          boolean m_bShowBackface
          Flag whether to show back facing elements whose element normal points always from camera.

        • m_bShowElementNormals

          Thickness in pixels of each element normal used in display.

        • m_globalElementNormalColor

          PdColor m_globalElementNormalColor
          Global color of element normals used in display.

        • m_bShowElementColors

          boolean m_bShowElementColors
          Flag if individual color of elements used in display.

        • m_globalElementColor

          PdColor m_globalElementColor
          Global color of elements used in display, applied if no individual element coloring available.

        • m_globalElementTagColor

          PdColor m_globalElementTagColor
          Global color of tagged elements used in display.

        • m_globalElementBackColor

          PdColor m_globalElementBackColor
          Global color of backside of elements used in display, applied if enabled.

        • m_bShowElementBackColor

          boolean m_bShowElementBackColor
          Flag to enable showing of separate backface color of elements.

        • m_bShowElementBackColors

          boolean m_bShowElementBackColors
          Flag if individual color of backside elements used in display.

        • m_bShowSmoothLighting

          boolean m_bShowSmoothLighting
          Flag if Gouraud shading is enabled.

        • m_bShowSmoothEdgeColors

          boolean m_bShowSmoothEdgeColors
          Flag if edges are smoothly shaded, currently requires vertex colors.

        • m_bShowSmoothElementColors

          boolean m_bShowSmoothElementColors
          Flag if elements are smoothly shaded, currently requires vertex colors.

        • m_bShowElementColorFromVertices

          boolean m_bShowElementColorFromVertices
          Flag if smooth element coloring uses vertex colors. Requires vertex colors.

    • Class jv.geom.PgPolygon extends PgPointSet implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • m_maxNumEdges

          int m_maxNumEdges
          Maximal number of edges of this polygon.

        • m_numEdges

          int m_numEdges
          Number of edges of this polygon. If polygon is closed then the number is equal to number of vertices of the pointSet. If the polygon is not closed then the number is equal to (number of vertices-1).

        • m_edge

          PiVector[] m_edge
          Index array determines the sequence of vertices in the polygon. If a polygon is not closed then the indices run in linear order thru the integers from 0 to numEdges referring to the vertices of the pointSet. If the polygon is closed then the last entry is 0 referring to the first vertex of the pointSet.

          The size of the edge array is one entry larger than maxNumVertices, since if polygon is closed then the array must also refer back to the first vertex.

          This is an internal variable and will automatically be filled.

        • m_edgeColor

          java.awt.Color[] m_edgeColor
          Array with a color of each edge. Size is always equal to maxNumVertices.

        • m_edgeNormal

          PdVector[] m_edgeNormal
          Array with a normal per edge. Size is always equal to maxNumVertices.

        • m_edgeSize

          PdVector m_edgeSize
          Thickness of each edge measured as radius of the representing circle or glyph.
          Since:
          JavaView 3.09

        • m_bShowEdgeSizes

          boolean m_bShowEdgeSizes
          Flag whether to show individual or global edge thickness.
          Since:
          JavaView 3.09

        • m_bClosed

          boolean m_bClosed
          Flag whether polygon is closed, i.e. last vertex is implicitly connected with an edge with the first vertex of the vertex array.
          See Also:
          PgPolygon.isClosed(), PgPolygon.setClosed(boolean)

        • m_bShowEdges

          boolean m_bShowEdges
          Flag whether polygon edges are shown in display.

        • m_bShowTaggedEdges

          boolean m_bShowTaggedEdges
          Flag whether tagged polygon edges are shown in display.

          boolean m_bShowEdgeLabels
          Flag whether labels of edges are shown in display.

          boolean m_bShowPolygonStartArrow
          Flag whether arrow is shown at first point of polygon.

          boolean m_bShowPolygonEndArrow
          Flag whether arrow is shown at last point of polygon.

          Flag whether edge colors are shown in display.

          PdColor m_globalEdgeColor
          Global color of polygons used in display, applied if no individual polygon coloring available.

        • m_globalEdgeTagColor

          PdColor m_globalEdgeTagColor
          Global color of tagged polygons used in display.

        • m_globalEdgeSize

          PuDouble m_globalEdgeSize
          Thickness in pixels of each edge of this polygon.

          boolean m_bShowEdgeNormals
          Flag whether to show edge normals or not.

          boolean m_bShowEdgeNormalArrow

        • m_blendingMode

          int m_blendingMode
          Determines the blending algorithm used to combine surface color and texture information.

        • m_surfaceSide

          int m_surfaceSide

        • m_periodic

          int m_periodic
          Determines if and how texture coordinates are interpreted which lie outside the normalized unit square. Value is one of PgGeometryIf.SIDE_BOTH, PgGeometryIf.PERIODIC_NONE, PgGeometryIf.PERIODIC_BOTH.

          Determines if pixel array still corresponds to selected image range.

          Dimension of simplicial complex, i.e. maximal dimension of occurring simplices. For example, polygonal curves have simplex dimension 1, triangulated surfaces 2, and volumes have 3. This variable must be set in the constructor of a class.
          Since:
          JavaView 1.95

          boolean m_bShowing
          Geometry is visible or hidden in its display.

          boolean m_bShowTitle
          Flag whether title is shown in display. The title of a geometry may be the same for several geometries of a scene indicating a grouping or other purposes.
          See Also:
          PsObject.setName(String), PgGeometry.showTitle(boolean), PgGeometry.setTitle(String)

          Flag whether title is shown in display. The title of a geometry may be the same for several geometries of a scene indicating a grouping or other purposes.
          Since:
          JavaView 2.47
          See Also:
          PsObject.setName(String), PgGeometry.showName(boolean), PgGeometry.setTitle(String)

        • m_bShowBndBox

          boolean m_bShowBndBox
          Flag whether bounding box is shown in display.

        • m_bShowCenter

          boolean m_bShowCenter
          Flag whether center is shown in display.

        • m_center

          PdVector m_center
          Center of geometry's world coordinate system

        • m_ambientSpace

          int m_ambientSpace
          Ambient space used in transformations of model. The dimension of the ambient space must be equal to the dimension of vertices.

        • m_ambientProj

          int m_ambientProj
          Projection from ambient space to R3 used in transformations of model.

        • m_modelMatrix

          PdMatrix m_modelMatrix
          4*4 model matrix of geometry, allocated on request.

        • m_ambientMatrix

          PdMatrix m_ambientMatrix
          Matrix for transformation of geometry within ambient space, allocated on request. Dimension of matrix is equal to dimension of vertices+1.

        • m_ambientInvMatrix

          PdMatrix m_ambientInvMatrix
          Inverse of ambient transformation matrix of geometry within ambient space, allocated on request. Dimension of matrix is equal to dimension of vertices+1.

        • m_labelAttribute

          PiVector[] m_labelAttribute
          Offset vector in pixel coordinates of label w.r.t. base point. There exist one vector for each of the basic primitive types GEOM_ITEM_POINT, GEOM_ITEM_EDGE,GEOM_ITEM_POLYGON,GEOM_ITEM_ELEMENT,GEOM_ITEM_TETRA, GEOM_ITEM_NAME and GEOM_ITEM_TITLE.

          Note, it is currently not possible to set the label attribute, say, of a single vertex unless you have a geometry with just one vertex.

          Third component is in [0..2] and indicates whether head, center or tail is located at base+offset. For possible types see PvGeometryIf#GEOM_ITEM_POINT and other items.

          Fourth component is a font id from the set of fonts available in PsConfig.

          The array contains offset, alignment and position information as follows: 

               m_labelAttribute[0] = xOffset;
     m_labelAttribute[1] = yOffset;
     m_labelAttribute[2] = horAdjust;
     m_labelAttribute[3] = verAdjust;
     m_labelAttribute[4] = font;

        • m_labelColor

          java.awt.Color[] m_labelColor
          Color of each label type.

        • m_labelSize

          PdVector m_labelSize
          Font size of each label type. Initial size is inherited from default size of fonts specified in PsConfig.

        • m_labelStyle

          PiVector m_labelStyle
          Font style of each label type. Initial style is inherited from default style of fonts specified in PsConfig.

        • m_labelFont

          java.lang.String[] m_labelFont
          Font name of each label type. If a name is missing then default font specified in PsConfig is used.

        • m_bInstanceSharing

          boolean m_bInstanceSharing
          Determines if sharing of vertices and other primitives with a based geometry is enabled when this instance is filled in PgGeomtry#getJvx().

          Scaling factor of all vectors.

          Shininess determines the specular exponent of highlights.

          Transparency is in [0, 1] where 0 corresponds to opaque and 1 to fully transparent.

          Flag is transparency is enabled.

          Number of components per texture coordinate.

          Flag whether to show element texture or not.

          Determines which sides of a surface receive texture if switched on. Value is one of PgGeometryIf.SIDE_BOTH, PgGeometryIf.SIDE_FRONT, PgGeometryIf.SIDE_BACK.

          int m_blendingMode
          Determines the blending algorithm used to combine surface color and texture information.

        • m_textureImageBnd

          PdVector[] m_textureImageBnd
          Texture coordinates of texture image, default is {(0,0),(1,1)}.

          Number of repetitions of texture image in both directions within the unit texture square, default is (1,1).

          int m_texturePeriodic
          Determines if texture periodically extends outside the unit texture square in none, both or either direction. Possible values are among PgGeometryIf#PERIODIC_BOTH etc.

        • m_bShowEdgeNormals

          boolean m_bShowEdgeNormals
          Flag whether to show edge normals or not.

        • m_bShowEdgeNormalArrow

          boolean m_bShowEdgeNormalArrow
          Flag whether arrows are shown at edge normals.

        • m_globalEdgeNormalLength

          double m_globalEdgeNormalLength
          Scaling factor of all edge normals used in display.

        • m_globalEdgeNormalSize

          double m_globalEdgeNormalSize
          Thickness in pixels of each edge normal used in display.

        • m_globalEdgeNormalColor

          java.awt.Color m_globalEdgeNormalColor
          Global color of edge normals used in display, applied if no individual normal coloring available.

        • m_creaseAngle

          double m_creaseAngle
          Crease angle is a threshold determining sharp crease edges. In smooth lighting and shading there is no interpolation across crease edges. An edge is a crease edge if the dihedral angle (positive angle between normals) between the two adjacent faces is equal or larger than the crease angle threshold. The crease angle is measure in radians in [0,Pi]. A crease angle 0 induces flat shading and prevents all smoothing, and a crease angle Pi+eps shows all edges with smooth shading.
          Since:
          JavaView 3.03.007

        • m_numPolygons

          int m_numPolygons
          Number of used polygons. Each polygon may be a polygon of different size.

        • m_maxNumPolygons

          int m_maxNumPolygons

        • m_dimOfPolygons

                                                = ..  all polygons are polygons with same size

        • m_lightDestBnd

          Stores light attenuation along boundary pixels of a face. Allocated in PvScene and shared by all geometries. For each pixel we have 6 values representing the light material and specular attenuation.

        • m_bndIdentifier

          PiVector m_bndIdentifier
          Determines the position of each boundary pixel of a face in the destination image, i.e. m_bndIdentifier.m_data[i] is a position in the [m_imgWidth, m_imgHeight] image. Identifier is used to reset boundary edge markers after drawScanline(). Identifier is shared by all geometries.

        • m_lightDestBnd

          int[][] m_lightDestBnd
          Stores light attenuation along boundary pixels of a face. Allocated in PvScene and shared by all geometries. For each pixel we have 6 values representing the light material and specular attenuation.

        • m_bndIdentifier

          PiVector m_bndIdentifier
          Determines the position of each boundary pixel of a face in the destination image, i.e. m_bndIdentifier.m_data[i] is a position in the [imgWidth, imgHeight] image. Identifier is used to reset boundary edge markers after drawScanline(). Identifier is shared by all geometries.

          int m_dimWithZBuffer
          Determines number of components of each vector which describes a scanline. First two components are the horizontal start and end pixel, third component is the z-depth in z-buffer mode, fourth component is the offset of the start and end pixel which avoids overlap with adjacent elements.

When mouse has left scene graph area, then m_bBeenHere is still true, and in consequence a last consume() of the event happens. In the calling PvDisplay.mouseMoved(MouseEvent) happens a last repaint() which removes the outline of the last node.

        • m_bShowingDialog

          boolean m_bShowingDialog
          Flag is true only during execution of method showDialog(int). This allows to suppress automatic selection of display when a dialog is shown. This seems to be a bug in Java since when the dialog is opened the associated frame is activated. Since the associated frame is PsConfig.getFrame(String) always the standard display was activated and could not be used in export.

        • m_bStarted

          boolean m_bStarted
          Flag determines whether PvViewer has been started or not. If viewer has not been started, then selecting a project does not start it. Instead, when PvViewer#start() is called, the currently selected project is started. This assures, that all setup in the PvViewer is done before the first project is started. Especially, the project can be sure that a display is created if the applet or application has requested it.

    • Class jvx.geom.PwNoise extends PjWorkshop implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • m_pointSet

          PgPointSet m_pointSet
          Original geometry which is disturbed with noise.

        • m_elemSet

          PgElementSet m_elemSet
          Additional reference to original geometry if instance of element set. This additional reference avoids multiple casts.

        • m_vertices

          PdVector[] m_vertices
          Vertices of original geometry.

        • m_normals

          PdVector[] m_normals
          Vertex normals of original geometry used to constrain noise direction.

        • m_noise

          PdVector[] m_noise
          Noise vectors added to vertices. The noise vector is scalar multiplied with the scalar factor m_eps when added to a vertex.

        • m_bNoise

          boolean[] m_bNoise
          Flag for each vertex if the vertex is modified or kept fix.

        • m_frequency

          PuInteger m_frequency
          Determines how many of the vertices are modified. If frequency is a number n then every n-th vertex is modified. By default, n is equal to 1, i.e. every vertex is modified.

        • m_eps

          PuDouble m_eps
          Scalar factor determines how much of the noise vectors is added to vertices.

        • m_bKeepBoundary

          boolean m_bKeepBoundary
          Flag if boundary vertices are kept fix.

        • m_bKeepSelected

          boolean m_bKeepSelected
          Flag if selected vertices are kept fix.

        • m_bTangential

          boolean m_bTangential
          Flag if tangential motion is allowed. Vertices move freely if normal and tangent motion is allowed.

        • m_bNormal

          boolean m_bNormal
          Flag if normal motion is allowed. Vertices move freely if normal and tangent motion is allowed.

        • m_bUpdateNormals

          boolean m_bUpdateNormals
          Flag if normal vectors of original geometry are updated when noise is added.

        • m_bHasElementNormals

          boolean m_bHasElementNormals
          Flag is original geometry has element normals.

        • m_bHasVertexNormals

          boolean m_bHasVertexNormals
          Flag is original geometry has vertex normals.

          Flag whether surface normals are updated after each minimization loop.

        • m_bUpdateDomain

          boolean m_bUpdateDomain
          Flag whether domain is updated after each CG-minization loop. When iteratively computing harmonic maps copy image surface into domain after minimization to update domain metric. Main use is inside Pinkall/Polthier algorithm on computing minimal surfaces by iterating harmonic maps.

        • m_jacobi

          PnJacobi m_jacobi
          Flag whether double or single precision is used in eigenvalue calculations. Single precision runs about two-times faster than double precision. The default behaviour is double precision.

        • m_bFixMarkedVertices

          PiVector m_snoe

          For each row of the full matrix exists an array listing the column position of each non-zero entry.

          PnSparseMatrix.m_stiff

        • m_stiff

          PdVector[] m_stiff
          For each row of the full matrix exists an array listing the non-zero values. The instance variable m_sindx has stored the column index. Therefore, the double component s[i][j] of the full matrix is stored in m_stiff[i][_j] if m_sindx[i][_j] == j.
          See Also:
          PnSparseMatrix.m_sindx

  • Package jvx.util

    • Class jvx.util.PuPriorityQueue extends PsObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • m_elements

          int[] m_elements
          Array contain the elements in the heap.

        • m_positions

          int[] m_positions
          Array contains the position where the element can be found the elements array, i.e. m_elements[m_positions[i]] = i and m_positions[m_elements[i]] = i.

        • m_keys

          double[] m_keys
          m_keys (resp. weights) of each element are stored. The key of element i can be found at m_keys[i], this means m_positions of the m_keys do not change when m_positions of the corresponding elements change.

        • m_capacity

          int m_capacity
          Maximum number of elements in the queue.

        • m_heapSize

          int m_heapSize
          Number of elements currently in the heap.

    • Class vgp.minimal.catenoid.PgCatenoid extends PgElementSet implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • m_bAlternate

          boolean m_bAlternate
          Flag to switch between regular, triangulated mesh, and a mesh whose vertical edges are zig-zag.

        • m_bTrueInterpolant

          boolean m_bTrueInterpolant
          If true then the catenoid parameters are chosen such that the discrete catenoid interpolates the smooth catenoid.

        • m_bFixedHeight

          boolean m_bFixedHeight
          Fix the distance between both horizontal catenoid rings on top and bottom. If height is fixed and the profile discretization modified then the distance between two successive rings measured by m_delta is adjusted. If flag is false then incrementing the profile discretization leads to a taller catenoid.

        • m_bSymmetric

          boolean m_bSymmetric
          Ensure that catenoid is symmetric with respect to horizontal plane. If true then the variable height of the bottom ring is automatically adjusted, and its slider is disabled.

        • m_height

          double m_height

        • m_bClosed

          boolean m_bClosed
          Close interior boundary of catenoid.

        • m_delta

          PuDouble m_delta
          Distance between two successive rings of the catenoid, constant for discrete catenoids.

        • m_bottomHeight

          PuDouble m_bottomHeight
          Vertical offset of lower ring for asymmetric catenoid.

        • m_radius

          PuDouble m_radius
          Radius of Catenoid Waist. For discrete catenoids the radius is defined as the zero value of the corresponding cosh curve.

        • m_k

          PuInteger m_k
          Dihedral symmetry of catenoid, number of meridians.

        • m_n

          PuInteger m_n
          Number of rings of catenoid.

        • m_defDelta

          double m_defDelta
          Default value of distance between two rings.

        • m_defBottomHeight

          double m_defBottomHeight
          Default value of vertical offset of lower ring for asymmetric catenoid.

        • m_defRadius

          double m_defRadius
          Default value of catenoid waist.

        • m_defK

          int m_defK
          Default number of meridians.

        • m_defN

          int m_defN
          Default number of rings.

  • Package vgp.minimal.helicoid

    • Class vgp.minimal.helicoid.PaHelicoid extends PsApplet implements Serializable

    • Class vgp.minimal.helicoid.PgHelicoid extends PgElementSet implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • m_bAlternate

          boolean m_bAlternate
          Flag to switch between regular, triangulated mesh, and a mesh whose vertical edges are zig-zag.

        • m_bFixedHeight

          boolean m_bFixedHeight
          Fix the distance between both horizontal helicoid lines on top and bottom. If height is fixed and the axis discretization modified then the distance between two successive lines measured by m_torsion is adjusted. If flag is false then incrementing the axis discretization leads to a taller helicoid.

        • m_bFixedWidth

          boolean m_bFixedWidth
          Fix the distance along a horizontal helicoid line. If width is fixed and the line discretization modified then the distance between two successive ticks on a line measured by m_lineDel is adjusted. If flag is false then incrementing the line discretization leads to a thinner helicoid.

        • m_bSymmetric

          boolean m_bSymmetric
          Ensure that helicoid is symmetric with respect to the central axis. If true then the variable height of the bottom ring is automatically adjusted, and its slider is disabled.

        • m_width

          double m_width
          Store current width if width is fixed.

        • m_height

          double m_height
          Store current height if height is fixed.

        • m_heightFac

          double m_heightFac
          If we are in fixed height mode, then heightFac given by heightFac =!= axisDel/sin(torsion) must remain constant when heightDel changes in order to keep the width of the helicoid. This is accomplished by adjusting the torsion. m_heightFac = m_axisDel/Math.sin(m_torsion.getValue());

        • m_lineDel

          PuDouble m_lineDel
          Distance between two horizontal ticks of the helicoid, constant for discrete helicoids.

        • m_xOffset

          PuDouble m_xOffset
          Vertical offset of lower ring for unsymmetric helicoid.

        • m_axisDel

          PuDouble m_axisDel
          Distance between two horizontal lines along the axis of the helicoid, constant for discrete helicoids.

        • m_torsion

          PuDouble m_torsion
          Torsion of the helicoid given as angle.

        • m_numAxisTicks

          PuInteger m_numAxisTicks
          Axis discretization of helicoid, i.e. number of ticks along vertical axis.

        • m_numLineTicks

          PuInteger m_numLineTicks
          Line discretization of helicoid, i.e. number of ticks along horizontal line.

        • m_defLineDelta

          double m_defLineDelta
          Default value of distance between two rings.

        • m_defXOffset

          double m_defXOffset
          Default value of horizontal offset from the z-axis.

        • m_defAxisDelta

          double m_defAxisDelta
          Default value of distance between two horizontal lines.

        • m_defTorsion

          double m_defTorsion
          Default value of the helicoid torsion.

        • m_defK

          int m_defK
          Default number of axis ticks.

        • m_defN

          int m_defN
          Default number of line ticks.

    • Class vgp.tutor.linear.PjLinear extends PjProject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • m_vectors

          PgPolygonSet m_vectors
          Two argument vectors are represented as two lines of a polygon set determined by their endpoints. The base point of both vectors is identical, namely, the first vertex of the polygon set. The second and third vertex of the polygon set are the endpoints of both vertices.

        • m_result

          PgPolygon m_result
          The result vector is a single polygon. The base point of this vector is kept equal to the base point of the two argument vectors, and its endpoint is computed from the two argument vectors depending on the current mode, i.e. either the sum, difference or cross product.

        • m_mode

          int m_mode
          Computation mode, possibly values are MODE_... constants.
